The paper discusses the use of Software Defined Networking (SDN) to improve the performance of Networked Music Performance (NMP) applications, which are ultra-low delay sensitive. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. Additionally, the paper proposes a collaboration between the network and NMP applications, which could fall under the System and Control (cs.SY) category. The use of SDN also suggests that the paper could belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) category. The paper also mentions signal processing and network delay, which could fall under the Multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the paper proposes a solution that achieves an improvement in delay, which could fall under the Information Theory (cs.IT) category.
